RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAZIA pressured GIRL OF MY DREAMS from outside, moved up on even terms around the bend, took over at the quarter pole, put away inner rival in upper stretch under right handed urging, drew away while racing a bit green and on the wrong lead but still remained clear to the wire. SHE'S A TEMPEST shifted in toward the extended rail leaving the chute but was quickly corrected, stalked from inside then two wide into the lane, came out and bumped rival at the eighth pole and kept on to best the rest. AFFAIR tracked between rivals early, rounded the bend two then three wide outside a rivals, got bumped by SHE'S A TEMPEST at the eighth pole and kept to task to edge GIRL OF MY DREAMS for the show. GIRL OF MY DREAMS stepped to the front and showed the way early under pressure from GRAZIA, dueled with that rival around the turn, relinquished the lead at the quarter pole, yielded to that rival in upper stretch, weakened in deep stretch and was edged for the show. AIR FORCE THUNDER broke a step slow, stalked outside a pair of rivals to the turn, lost ground under a ride and exited the bend four wide, then weakened in the stretch.

ENTRY.OWNER: Beerman Family Trust and Sayjay Racing LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: shifted in early, stalked inside-2wide, came out/bumped 1/8

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 102. Starter Allowance Purse 36000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS IN 2022-2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TABLE FOR TEN rated in the two path, bid three deep on the far turn, got floated out a bit into the lane, took over in upper stretch, held a short advantage into the final sixteenth and won the bob over MO REWARDS at the wire. MO REWARDS tracked the pace from the rail to the far turn, tipped two wide near the quarter pole, angled out widest, rallied and drew alongside TABLE FOR TEN past the sixteenth pole but was outnodded on the line. RED CROSS KNIGHT had good early speed and led in the two path around the first turn then moved over to the rail, took pressure in the middle stages, vied with outer pair with a quarter mile remaining, lost command in upper stretch but stayed on well for a game third. JAMMING EDDY stalked from inside then switched to the outside of the pacesetter approaching the backstretch, pressed up the backstretch, gained the advantage past the quarter pole, came out a bit at the top of the lane, lost command in upper stretch and faltered late. ZIMBA WARRIOR settled at the back in the two path, exited the second bend three wide, moved back in a bit in upper stretch, chased within striking range through the final furlong but needed to find more late.

ENTRY.OWNER: Mia Familia Racing Stable and Ward Dudley
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside-2wide, pressed outside, led, faltered

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 85. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREAT FORTY EIGHT stalked two then three wide on the first turn, closed in tandem with FLYNN'S CHANCE on the far turn and challenged three deep at the quarter pole, took over late on the bend, cleared inner rival in upper stretch and held safely under urging. NAFISA chased four wide around the first turn, trailed two wide into the second bend, moved inside while advancing then steered back out and came three wide into the stretch, rallied and nailed FLYNN'S CHANCE for the place honors. FLYNN'S CHANCE settled along the rail off the pace, on the move through the far turn, tipped two wide and challenged between rivals approaching the quarter pole, gained command briefly before being overtaken by GREAT FORTY EIGHT late on the turn, kept on through the lane but got edged for second at the wire. PACIFIC ROSE bobbled leaving the gate, traveled two wide outside a rival at the back early, went between rivals in the middle stages, got put in a bit tight entering the far turn, moved out to the three path and had little left for the drive. GREER MY DEAR chased three deep into the first turn then got moved out to the four path, continued wide through the second bend and weakened down the lane. ELEGANT sprinted clear and moved inside then two wide on the first turn, opened up on the backstretch, grew weary on the far turn and was reeled in at the quarter pole, tired in the lane and eased to the wire and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Pacific Rose
ENTRY.OWNER: California Racing Partners Ciaglia Racing LLC and Savides Domenic
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled, 2wide, bit tight 7/16, 3wide into str, empty

DOLLY MAY (IRE) restless in the gate, traveled near the back along the rail, made progress on the fence through the far turn, went between rivals at the eighth pole and failed to menace. TICKLE MY FANCY antsy in the gate, stalked from inside then began to pull and rushed up between rivals into the clubhouse turn, bumped at the nine-sixteenths pole, applied pressure on the backstretch then chased into the far turn, continued in the two path to the stretch and weakened down the lane. ROPERS N WRANGLERS cleared quickly and crossed over to the inside, vied with rivals into the first turn then assumed control once again, showed the way under pressure in the middle stages, cleared leaving the backstretch, challenged by the winner at the quarter pole, lost command approaching the stretch and faded in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 89. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICAN HOPE prominent three deep into the first turn then pressed the pace two wide into the backstretch, dueled two then three wide on the far turn, inched ahead in upper stretch, cleared past the sixteenth pole and held the runner-up at bay. EL REY REY reserved early then started to pull and was a bit rank while moving inside, went two wide into the far turn, shifted out and bumped SHOT OF COURAGE midway through the bend, angled four wide into the stretch, closed from outside but was too late. POTENTIAL SPAM sat off the pace two wide, moved closer up the backstretch, came three wide into the lane and gained the show. BANDWAGON had early speed between rivals into the first turn then ceded command and stalked in the two path, moved inside for the second bend, chased two wide into the lane, moved out in the drive and finished willingly. TRIBAL vied with outer rivals into the first turn then took control around the bend, set the pace under pressure, dueled on the far turn, overtaken at the top of the lane, stayed on to the sixteenth pole and weakened late. GOLD FOOT stalked from inside then tracked out of range in the middle stages, saved ground through the far turn, tipped two wide into the lane, kept to task through the lane and found traffic briefly late but failed to threaten. SHOT OF COURAGE fractious in the gate, was off slow and broke out, traveled two wide early, three deep on the backstretch, got bumped midway around the far turn, floated five wide into the lane and came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANCERY WAY quickly took control from inside, set all the pace to the stretch, put to right handed urging and remained well clear to the wire. ROSE DAWSON bobbled and broke outward before being corrected, stalked outside rivals, went five wide into the turn, advanced around the bend, chased four wide into the lane, could not threaten the winner in the late stages but finished willingly to best the rest. CARMEN MIRANDA hit the gate and broke in a bit at the start, stalked four wide into the turn, exited the bend three wide, lacked the needed late punch when called upon and got outkicked for second. GLORIOUS SPRING broke out and bumped SMOOTHLIKEBUTTAH, tracked along the inside into the turn, remained along the fence and cut the corner into the lane, moved out in upper stretch and kept on to improve position. CHISMOSA broke a bit slow and got bumped at the start, chased off the pace then moved closer up the backstretch, went between rivals but got put in tight at the three-eighths pole, tipped three wide into the clear on the bend, steered out in upper stretch and could not rally. BELLA D raced up close early off the inside, chased two wide around the bend and weakened. SMOOTHLIKEBUTTAH got sandwiched between rivals at the start, trailed on the inside into the turn, spun three wide into the drive and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALI BAY (IRE) traveled two wide outside a rival near the back, angled out approaching the quarter pole, came five wide into the stretch, surged clear at the eighth pole and powered away under right handed encouragement and steady handling in deep stretch. TAISHAN raced on the inside towards the rear, ran into traffic briefly at the quarter pole, split foes leaving the bend, bumped inner rival at the top of the stretch, angled to the inside at the eighth pole and rallied for second. SOULMATE was off a bit slow and bothered leaving the gate, went up to press the pace from outside, took over at the five-sixteenths pole and cleared quickly, moved over to the inside, offered no resistance to the winner at the eighth pole and flattened to third. JACKS OUTLAW rated along the rail early, tipped two wide on the far turn, chased within range entering the final furlong but needed to find more late. SUBSIDIZE broke a step slow, stalked four then three wide early, traveled three deep leaving the backstretch, four deep at the quarter pole and weakened down the lane. NAUVOO showed keen early foot pulling early, set the pace under pressure from outer rival, lost command at the five-sixteenths pole, failed to fight back and chased the new leader into the lane, took a bump from outside and steadied at the top of the stretch and faded.
